The special arrangement of individuals, irregularly dichotomously branching style, variable body shape, apically located contractile vacuole, high number of silverlines and marine habitat of the current population matches well to the holotype , which was found as an ectocommensal organism on the shrimp (
Song 1991 a
) (Figs. 3 B, 3 C). In original description, the P 3 was described as having only two rows of kineties (Fig.
3 I
). Based on a reexamination on the holotype , the peniculus 3 is composed of three rows which matched hence the present form.
